radiographic_examinations.findings: Complex, solid mass measuring 3.0 cm by 2.9 cm by 2.9 cm in the lower pole of the right kidney with heterogeneous signal intensity. Loss of signal at the posterior aspect of the lesion consistent with the presence of intravoxel fat. The mass was suspicious for renal carcinoma.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: The renal mass was previously noted to be approximately 2.8 cm by 2.6 cm by 2.5 cm on an abdominal ultrasound examination performed 1.5 years earlier.
